<reference id="topic" xml:lang="en-us">
<title>topic</title>
<shortdesc>The &lt;<keyword>topic</keyword>&gt; element is the top-level
DITA element for a single-subject topic or article. Other top-level
DITA elements that are more content-specific are &lt;<keyword>concept</keyword>&gt;, &lt;<keyword>task</keyword>&gt;, &lt;<keyword>reference</keyword>&gt;,
and &lt;<keyword>glossentry</keyword>&gt;, all of which are specializations
of the &lt;topic> element.</shortdesc><?Pub Caret -1?>
